		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>Emblazoned with the holy symbol of Bahamut, this platinum blade empowers the wielder to unleash divine retribution upon enemies while bolstering his or her allies.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Weapon</b><b>:</b> Heavy blade</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +5d10 critical damage</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Property:</b></p> <p>If you worship Bahamut, you can use this weapon as a holy symbol. It adds its enhancement bonus (but not its proficiency bonus) to attack rolls and damage rolls when used in this manner. If you do not worship Bahamut, you do not benefit from this weapon's property and cannot use this weapon's power.</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power âœ¦ Daily (Standard Action)</b></p><p>Close blast 5; targets enemies; Charisma vs. Reflex (apply a bonus to the attack roll equal to the weapon's enhancement bonus); 2d8 + Charisma modifier force damage. Allies in the blast take no damage and regain hit points equal to your Wisdom modifier + your Charisma modifier.</p><p>Level 29: 3d8 + Charisma modifier force damage.</p>",
